
[1]crave

   CRAVE, v.t.

   1. To ask with earnestness or importunity; to beseech; to implore; to
   ask with submission or humility, as a dependent; to beg; to entreat.

   As for my nobler friends, I crave their pardons.

   Joseph--went in boldly to Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus. Mark
   15.

   2. To call for, as a gratification; to long for; to require or demand,
   as a passion or appetite; as, the stomach or appetite craves food.

   3. Sometimes intransitively, with for before the thing sought; as, I
   crave for mercy.
